                  <div class="portfolio-item-individual">
                      <h3>Zendesk Support</h3>
                    <p>I've worked with Zendesk Dashboard for a while now. I've got my first promotion mainly because of it. I've worked with Automations, Triggers, Macros, API's and more. Recently after proving myself our client has given me full admin permissions to Zendesk. I've single handedly installed different Macros, Triggers, and Automations to provide support and route incoming volume to its respectful "views". I'm pretty confident with Zendesk Dashboard, and I'm quite excited to work with it's extention "Sunshine" it's mostly build towards developers and give us more freedome to create and update.</p>
                    <h3>Zendesk Chat</h3>
                    <p>After working and developing the chatbot flows we finally launched the our Chatbot last year, and I was given the oportunity to explore more of Zendesk Chat, linking the chatbot to the Zendesk Chat developing new tags, macros and triggers to ease up agents work and route the incoming chats to its respectful teams/languages.</p>
                    <h3>Zendesk Help Center (KB)</h3>
                    <p>This is where I spent most of my day, developing new articles with my html/css/javascript knowledge, working towards creating new layouts and contents, to provide less reading material and more CTA (Call to Action) buttons. My main focus is to provide all the details agents needs to know inside one article(process) in best way. I'm trying to remove the article base were we add ton of text and we expect the agents to read it, and work towards flow they can follow.</p>
